          <h2>Privacy Policy</h2>

          <div class="privacy-content">
            <article>
              <h3>1. Information We Collect</h3>
              <p>
                We collect personal information including name, email, phone
                number, and educational background during registration and
                course enrollment.
              </p>

              <h3>2. Use of Information</h3>
              <p>Your information is used for:</p>
              <ul>
                <li>Course administration and communication</li>
                <li>Certificate issuance</li>
                <li>Educational updates and newsletters</li>
                <li>Academic record maintenance</li>
              </ul>

              <h3>3. Data Security</h3>
              <p>
                We implement industry-standard security measures to protect your
                personal information from unauthorized access or disclosure.
              </p>

              <h3>4. Information Sharing</h3>
              <p>
                We do not sell or share your personal information with third
                parties except as required for educational partnerships and
                certifications.
              </p>

              <h3>5. Cookies and Tracking</h3>
              <p>
                Our website uses cookies to enhance user experience and analyze
                website traffic.
              </p>

              <h3>6. Student Rights</h3>
              <p>Students have the right to:</p>
              <ul>
                <li>Access their personal data</li>
                <li>Request data corrections</li>
                <li>Opt-out of marketing communications</li>
                <li>
                  Request data deletion (subject to academic record
                  requirements)
                </li>
              </ul>

              <h3>7. Data Retention</h3>
              <p>
                We retain student records as required by educational regulations
                and for certification verification purposes.
              </p>

              <h3>8. Third-Party Services</h3>
              <p>
                We may use third-party services for payment processing, email
                communication, and learning management systems.
              </p>

              <h3>9. Policy Updates</h3>
              <p>
                This privacy policy may be updated periodically. Users will be
                notified of significant changes.
              </p>

              <h3>10. Contact Information</h3>
              <p>
                For privacy-related inquiries, contact us at
                <a href="mailto:privacy@fstn.org">editorialfstn@gmail.com</a>
              </p>
            </article>
